y 30 percent of Nazi Germany's petroleum. The missions were notorious: Operation Tidal Wave in August 1943 lost 54 aircraft in a single low-level run and produced five Medal of Honor recipients — the most awarded for any single action in WWII.","number":1},{"header":"He presided over a school desegregation case","body":"Berry v. School District of the City of Benton Harbor began in the 1970s and wound through the federal courts for decades. Hillman took over the case, issued a comprehensive remedial order in 1981 mandating compensatory education, busing adjustments, and faculty diversification — rejecting inter-district mergers as too disruptive.","number":2},{"header":"He co-founded the World Affairs Council of Western","body":"In 1949, just two years after passing the bar, Douglas Hillman co-founded the World Affairs Council of Western Michigan alongside businessman Edgar Orr. Their mission was to heighten global awareness among Americans, with a particular focus on engaging younger generations through lectures and cultural exchange. The Hillman-Orr Award, named jointly for both founders, continues today, honoring regional contributions to international understanding.","number":3}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Chief Judge Douglas Woodruff Hillman","first_name":"Douglas","last_name":"Hillman","middle_name":"Woodruff","title":"Chief Judge","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"douglas-hillman-1922"},"HD2511":{"id":"HD2511","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":11,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"X00822","mother_id":"HD2500"},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1926},"death":{"